The floral evidence agrees with a general increase in drainage from the Fruitland to Kirtland. The abundance of medium-sized angiospermous leaves with entire or nearly entire margins and drip points suggests a warm-temperature to subtropical climate during deposition of both formations by analogy with modern floras (
Lucas , 1981
;
Tidwell et al ., 1981
;
Robison et al., 1982
).
